    • Method Detail

      • buildEObject

        org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject buildEObject(com.mongodb.DBCollection collection,
                                         com.mongodb.DBObject dbObject,
                                         org.eclipse.emf.ecore.resource.Resource resource,
                                         boolean isProxy)
        Build an EMF EObject from the supplied DBObject from MongoDB.
        Parameters:
        collection - the MongoDB collection containing the DBObject
        dbObject - the object read from MongoDB
        resource - the resource that will contain the EMF Object This function will not add the created to the supplied resource to support the case where the user wishes to return a collection of objects such as the result of a query.
        isProxy - true if the object is to be built as a proxy; false otherwise
        Returns:
        the newly created EMF object instance
